Huber: less sensitive to outliers than least-squares. It is equivalent to
least squares when \(|y_i - f(x_i)| \leq \varepsilon\) , and \(L(y_i, f(x_i)) = \varepsilon |y_i - f(x_i)| - \frac{1}{2}
\varepsilon^2\) otherwise.

